Action: Answer("B") 
Thought: 
  Let the height of the room be 2x meters and its semi-perimeter be 5x meters.
  Then, 2x/5x = 2/5.
  Therefore, x = 2.5.
  The height of the room is 2x = 5 meters.
  The area of the walls is 2h(l + b) = 2 * 5(5x + 5x) = 50x sq.m.
  The area of the walls excluding doors and windows is 50x - 15 = 50 * 2.5 - 15 = 110 sq.m.
  The length of the paper required is 110/0.5 = 220 m.
  The cost of papering the walls is Rs.220 * 2 = Rs.440.
  Therefore, the height of the room is 3.9m.

Thought:
  The frog jumps 3m up one day and falls back 2m down the same day.
  So, the net progress of the frog in one day is 3m - 2m = 1m.
  The frog needs to cover 30m to come out of the well.
  Therefore, the number of days it will take for the frog to come out of the well is 30m / 1m/day = 30 days.
  However, on the 30th day, the frog will jump 3m up and will not fall back down.
  Therefore, the frog will come out of the well on the 29th day.
  The answer is E: 29 days.

Thought:
  a2 - b2/(a + b)2 = (a - b)2
  Multiplying both sides by (a + b)2, we get:
  a2 - b2 = (a - b)2(a + b)2
  Expanding the right side, we get:
  a2 - b2 = (a2 - 2ab + b2)(a2 + 2ab + b2)
  Expanding the right side again, we get:
  a2 - b2 = a4 + 2a2b2 + b4 - 2a3b - 2ab3 - 2a2b2
  Simplifying, we get:
  a2 - b2 = a4 - 2a3b + 2a2b2 - 2ab3 + b4
  Therefore, the answer is A: (a + b)(a - b).
Action: Answer("A")

  The relationship between primary substances and secondary substances is most similar to the relationship between mechanical components and electrical components in clothing factories.
  Therefore, the answer is C: Mechanical components such as gears and rotors are required for the operation of clothing factories; electrical components such as wires and transformers supply the power needed to run the mechanical components, but they do not participate directly in the manufacturing process.

  $$20 \text{ grams} \times \frac{1,000 \text{ milligrams}}{1 \text{ gram}} = 20,000 \text{ milligrams}$$

  Streptococcus mutans is a bacterium that is commonly found in the human mouth.
  It is a major cause of dental caries (cavities).
  MacConkey agar is a selective medium that is used to isolate gram-negative bacteria.
  Mitis salivarius bacitracin agar (MSB agar) is a selective medium that is used to isolate Streptococcus mutans.
  Nutrient agar is a non-selective medium that can be used to grow a wide variety of bacteria.
  Tellurite medium is a selective medium that is used to isolate Corynebacterium diphtheriae.
  Therefore, the most used selective medium for Streptococcus mutans is Mitis salivarius bacitracin agar.
  The answer is B: Mitus salivarius bacitracin agar.
